        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2761686482" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer10945635925845789067">This book covered way too much time and in too much detail. McCaffrey wrote an introduction stating that she wrote this book to explain some things that had happened in Pern before the books she had already wrote. I didn&apos;t feel like this gave any needed material to the world of Pern. Yes, we learn some of the specifics of events that were alluded to, but none of them are critical. This book had potential to be interesting even with this issue as Robinton is a fascinating character, yet somehow, </span>
  <span id="freeText10945635925845789067" style="display:none">This book covered way too much time and in too much detail. McCaffrey wrote an introduction stating that she wrote this book to explain some things that had happened in Pern before the books she had already wrote. I didn't feel like this gave any needed material to the world of Pern. Yes, we learn some of the specifics of events that were alluded to, but none of them are critical. This book had potential to be interesting even with this issue as Robinton is a fascinating character, yet somehow, his story fell flat. I think it was partly the shear amount of time covered.</span>
  <a data-text-id="10945635925845789067" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

