    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_1146247296" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1146247296" />
    <a title="Aishuu" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/38410238-aishuu"><img alt="Aishuu" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1419983957p2/38410238.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1146247296?book_show_action=true">Dec 29, 2014</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Aishuu" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Aishuu" href="/user/show/38410238-aishuu">Aishuu</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/38410238-aishuu?shelf=read-perm-collection-hardcover">read-perm-collection-hardcover</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1146247296" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer8130202285097529673">I&apos;m rereading the Pern books because I was nostalgic. This book remained in my collection, but I still can&apos;t give it a great review. As much as I love Robinton, this book is the ultimate retconn.<br/><br/>As I&apos;ve been rereading Pern, the inconsistencies (and typos and name issues!) really began to bother me. I had to wonder who the heck was editing, because there was no cross-checking, and things just don&apos;t fit together right.<br/><br/>I liked this book, but I have to consider it a fanfic of Pern rather than direct</span>
  <span id="freeText8130202285097529673" style="display:none">I'm rereading the Pern books because I was nostalgic. This book remained in my collection, but I still can't give it a great review. As much as I love Robinton, this book is the ultimate retconn.<br /><br />As I've been rereading Pern, the inconsistencies (and typos and name issues!) really began to bother me. I had to wonder who the heck was editing, because there was no cross-checking, and things just don't fit together right.<br /><br />I liked this book, but I have to consider it a fanfic of Pern rather than direct canon. It doesn't fit with the rest of the series. I'm sure other people have pointed out issues, but these were the ones that really threw me out of the story:<br /><br />*Petiron - There's no way the kindly old harper from the Harper Hall books could have come from him. Aside from him saying their were no girl harpers (surprising, since he's so into female singers), Shonagar says that he can't do voice training... which is a major part of this arc. And so forth and so forth....<br /><br />*Sebell - Twenty years too early for him. In HH, it's frequently mentioned that he just walked the tables when he meets Menolly, which he becomes a journeyman about twenty years before.<br /><br />*Timeline inconsistencies galore. There's a lot that's been shoehorned in to make Robinton the center of attention, but it doesn't work when compared to any of the books written previously.</span>
  <a data-text-id="8130202285097529673" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


