<div id="review_2132272067" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2132272067" />
    <a title="Jeff Suter" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/24951864-jeff-suter"><img alt="Jeff Suter" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1382529144p2/24951864.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2132272067?book_show_action=true">Sep 22, 2017</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Jeff Suter" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Jeff Suter" href="/user/show/24951864-jeff-suter">Jeff Suter</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was ok"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was ok</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback " href="/book/show/12356196-the-masterharper-of-pern">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2132272067" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer12844888513712808749">This should have been a wonderful book, it&apos;s about Robinton one of the most likeable characters in the Pern books. But I am sorry to say Anne McCaffrey blew it big time. Of course this was at the height of the publish anything with &quot;Dragon&quot; in the title mania. It wouldn&apos;t be so bad if McCaffrey stayed true to her own plots and continuity. With Masterharper she totally destroys plot and continuity. <br/><br/>Continuity glitch #1: Robinton&apos;s mother is a Harper? Since when? Remember Menolly? - She was a sham</span>
  <span id="freeText12844888513712808749" style="display:none">This should have been a wonderful book, it's about Robinton one of the most likeable characters in the Pern books. But I am sorry to say Anne McCaffrey blew it big time. Of course this was at the height of the publish anything with "Dragon" in the title mania. It wouldn't be so bad if McCaffrey stayed true to her own plots and continuity. With Masterharper she totally destroys plot and continuity. <br /><br />Continuity glitch #1: Robinton's mother is a Harper? Since when? Remember Menolly? - She was a shameful thing, a girl that played music. A disgrace, an aberration - GIRLS COULDN'T BE HARPERS. The shame was so bad that Menolly's own mother tried to stop her playing ability by trying to ensure her wounded hand would not heal properly thus stopping her playing the guitar. <br /><br />Glitch#2 (And the most glaring). As a youth Robinton can talk to dragons, any dragon. This is a big deal, it is established in Dragonquest that this is a rare gift and usually confined to Weyrwomen. In Dragonquest Lessa tells Robinton that only two people on Pern can talk to any dragon, herself and Brekke. It is a very useful trait that would have aided F'Lar and Lessa in their plans to save Pern. Only Robinton seems to have "forgotten" that he can do this. He hears dragons, but thinks it is human voices. In the White Dragon, the dragons all speak directly to Robinton to stop him dying from his heart attack. Robinton is surprised about this. Now also remember that Pernese people are in awe of dragons, everyone dreams of being a dragonrider. Everyone wants to talk and be linkd to those magnificent creatures. Even owning a fire lizard is an unrequited wish. Yet Robinton has forgotten his ability to commune with dragons. I wouldn't, would you?<br /><br />Masterharper of Pern is a very flawed book. I think the 2 stars I gave it is over-generous. I only consider the three main titles and the YA parallel series (Menolly/Piemur) to be canon, all the rest can be safely ignored, especially Masterharper of Pern.</span>
  <a data-text-id="12844888513712808749" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


