<div id="review_1825052753" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1825052753" />
    <a title="Adrian Rose" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/41342610-adrian-rose"><img alt="Adrian Rose" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1550175761p2/41342610.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1825052753?book_show_action=true">Dec 24, 2019</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Adrian Rose" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Adrian Rose" href="/user/show/41342610-adrian-rose">Adrian Rose</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/41342610-adrian-rose?shelf=scifi-fantasy">scifi-fantasy</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1825052753" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer16959647620533570876">In the first books of the Pern saga that were published, there is a man named Robinton, who is the Master of Harpers, the institution that is responsible for not only entertaining at festivals but also for educating the population in things like reading, arithmetic, and understanding their civil rights and responsibilities. Robinton is not a main character, but, as the story progresses, he becomes one of the best beloved of the supporting cast. This book is his story.<br/>A musical prodigy since the </span>
  <span id="freeText16959647620533570876" style="display:none">In the first books of the Pern saga that were published, there is a man named Robinton, who is the Master of Harpers, the institution that is responsible for not only entertaining at festivals but also for educating the population in things like reading, arithmetic, and understanding their civil rights and responsibilities. Robinton is not a main character, but, as the story progresses, he becomes one of the best beloved of the supporting cast. This book is his story.<br />A musical prodigy since the age of three, Robinton is the product of the marriage between a beautiful but frail soprano and a demanding, uncaring composer. He is raised in Harper Hall, the headquarters of the Harpers. As he grows, the tension between his parents leads to his being sheltered and protected by the other Harpers, and his genius going unrecognized by the man from whom he wishes approval the most. This story follows him through his life, his coming of age and tragic love, and his unwavering devotion to and friendship with the Dragonriders that protect his home from the incursions of Thread that brings devastation every couple of centuries or so. For those who know and love Pern and its heroes, this book is a must, for it answers many questions about the history of that planet that are only mentioned in passing in the other books. McCaffrey works her usual magic in creating a wonderful and endearing world full of people that the reader cannot help but fall in love with. Absolutely stunning.<br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="16959647620533570876" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


